2744
01:27:53,934 --> 01:27:55,374
They just give me a thumbs-up. What?

2745
01:27:56,004 --> 01:27:57,004
Is that the car?

2746
01:27:58,104 --> 01:27:59,433
(One car pulled over.)

2747
01:27:59,434 --> 01:28:02,573
This car... Could you give me a ride?

2748
01:28:02,574 --> 01:28:04,673
Hello. This is 2 Days 1 Night.

2749
01:28:04,674 --> 01:28:06,314
- I'm Lee Joon.
- Hello.

2750
01:28:06,474 --> 01:28:09,344
- Thank you so much.
- My pleasure.

2751
01:28:09,884 --> 01:28:11,613
There's no car anyway.

2752
01:28:11,614 --> 01:28:12,653
(And Se Yoon was complaining to a citizen.)

2753
01:28:12,654 --> 01:28:13,824
This is my car.

2754
01:28:14,554 --> 01:28:15,584
Really?

2755
01:28:15,854 --> 01:28:17,054
Then, please give me a ride.

2756
01:28:17,394 --> 01:28:18,723
- Can you do that?
-Let's go.

2757
01:28:18,724 --> 01:28:20,793
- Can you really go there?
- Sure.

2758
01:28:20,794 --> 01:28:21,794
Seriously?

2759
01:28:21,795 --> 01:28:22,994
Shall we go then?

2760
01:28:23,534 --> 01:28:24,534
Thank you.

2761
01:28:24,535 --> 01:28:27,304
The other members are running around to look for it.

2762
01:28:27,764 --> 01:28:29,103
I'll quietly try...

2763
01:28:29,104 --> 01:28:31,104
to turn things around at the last minute.

2764
01:28:31,834 --> 01:28:34,374
So, do I have any chance of winning?

2765
01:28:34,904 --> 01:28:37,243
But I saw someone running ahead of us.

2766
01:28:37,244 --> 01:28:38,414
They ran?

2767
01:28:38,474 --> 01:28:41,014
It won't be easy to find it running around.

2768
01:28:41,714 --> 01:28:44,284
(The members in the lead are exhausted from running.)

2769
01:28:44,484 --> 01:28:46,644
You have to be a good athlete to be on 2 Days 1 Night.

2770
01:28:47,624 --> 01:28:49,024
This is 2 Days 1 Night.

2771
01:28:49,054 --> 01:28:50,124
Hello.

2772
01:28:50,824 --> 01:28:52,293
Do you know the place...

2773
01:28:52,294 --> 01:28:53,770
where "When the Camellia Blooms" was filmed?

2774
01:28:53,794 --> 01:28:54,894
It's over there.

2775
01:28:58,964 --> 01:29:00,763
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2776
01:29:00,764 --> 01:29:02,403
(It turns out it was right in front of them!)

2777
01:29:02,404 --> 01:29:05,374
(They run at full speed again.)

2778
01:29:05,604 --> 01:29:07,203
(Seon Ho, DinDin)

2779
01:29:07,204 --> 01:29:08,574
(Now they know the direction.)

2780
01:29:08,904 --> 01:29:11,574
(Who will be faster?)

2781
01:29:11,914 --> 01:29:13,313
There are cameras.

2782
01:29:13,314 --> 01:29:14,383
I see the cameras,

2783
01:29:14,384 --> 01:29:15,784
but I can't find the place.

2784
01:29:16,584 --> 01:29:18,213
- There are cameras.
- There it is.

2785
01:29:18,214 --> 01:29:19,653
This is it. It's here.

2786
01:29:19,654 --> 01:29:21,454
The stairs are right over there.

2787
01:29:21,824 --> 01:29:23,023
Should I go up the stairs?

2788
01:29:23,024 --> 01:29:24,724
(I'm here as well.)

2789
01:29:25,094 --> 01:29:27,424
(Which one of them will arrive first?)

2790
01:29:27,594 --> 01:29:29,594
- Thank you so much.
- Bye.

2791
01:29:29,964 --> 01:29:31,794
- Bye.
- Bye.

2792
01:29:32,464 --> 01:29:35,164
(Once they pull out the flag on the top of the stairs, they win.)

2793
01:29:35,504 --> 01:29:39,274
(Who will win the One-Bite Ticket?)

2794
01:29:41,004 --> 01:29:43,944
(Seon Ho arrives at the stairs.)

2795
01:29:44,314 --> 01:29:47,983
(Seon Ho is a few steps ahead of DinDin.)

2796
01:29:47,984 --> 01:29:50,783
(Flag, Seon Ho, DinDin)

2797
01:29:50,784 --> 01:29:52,464
(Now, once he climbs the stairs, he wins.)

2798
01:29:55,484 --> 01:29:57,254
(Why is he going in the opposite direction?)

2799
01:30:00,194 --> 01:30:01,194
It's over there.

2800
01:30:01,924 --> 01:30:02,924
It's over there.

2801
01:30:02,964 --> 01:30:04,964
(How lucky!)

2802
01:30:05,194 --> 01:30:06,563
I came the wrong way.

2803
01:30:06,564 --> 01:30:07,564
(What a fool.)

2804
01:30:07,804 --> 01:30:09,103
(He came in 1st place by a lucky chance.)

2805
01:30:09,104 --> 01:30:10,304
I was almost there.

2806
01:30:10,774 --> 01:30:13,103
(While gasping for breath, )

2807
01:30:13,104 --> 01:30:15,644
(he enjoys his luck.)

2808
01:30:16,704 --> 01:30:17,843
I was almost there.

2809
01:30:17,844 --> 01:30:19,524
(A moment's choice determined the result.)

2810
01:30:19,844 --> 01:30:20,943
(DinDin won the One-Bite Ticket.)

2811
01:30:20,944 --> 01:30:22,344
Congratulations, DinDin.

2812
01:30:22,514 --> 01:30:24,114
Here's the One-Bite Ticket.

2813
01:30:25,314 --> 01:30:26,653
(Gasping)

2814
01:30:26,654 --> 01:30:28,324
I got here first,

2815
01:30:28,554 --> 01:30:29,623
but I didn't see the stairs.

2816
01:30:29,624 --> 01:30:31,454
I kept looking for the stairs.

2817
01:30:31,754 --> 01:30:33,224
That was so close.

2818
01:30:33,924 --> 01:30:35,324
I didn't make it.

2819
01:30:35,564 --> 01:30:36,693
You came running all the way here?

2820
01:30:36,694 --> 01:30:37,793
It's far.

2821
01:30:37,794 --> 01:30:40,334
I could've won if I found a ride a little faster.

2822
01:30:40,404 --> 01:30:42,333
I didn't run. I took the main road and found a ride right away.

2823
01:30:42,334 --> 01:30:43,534
That's why you came in fourth.

2824
01:30:44,174 --> 01:30:45,334
This is pretty.

2825
01:30:46,934 --> 01:30:48,174
It's so cool.

2826
01:30:48,244 --> 01:30:50,274
This is where the drama was filmed.

2827
01:30:50,544 --> 01:30:53,213
It's called Guryongpo Modern Culture and History Street.

2828
01:30:53,214 --> 01:30:55,854
(Guryongpo Modern Culture and History Street with a pretty sunset)

2829
01:30:56,714 --> 01:30:58,184
Should we wait for Jong Min?

2830
01:30:58,954 --> 01:31:00,213
Try calling Jong Min.

2831
01:31:00,214 --> 01:31:01,553
I called him, but he didn't answer.

2832
01:31:01,554 --> 01:31:02,554
(Jong Min is missing?)

2833
01:31:02,555 --> 01:31:03,724
Where are you, Jong Min?

2834
01:31:03,794 --> 01:31:04,993
I'm looking for the place now.

2835
01:31:04,994 --> 01:31:06,493
- Are you still looking for it?
- Yes.

2836
01:31:06,494 --> 01:31:08,724
- You'll have to hurry.
- Why?

2837
01:31:08,964 --> 01:31:10,124
We all got here already.

2838
01:31:10,894 --> 01:31:13,434
Really? I don't know where I am now.

2839
01:31:13,804 --> 01:31:15,734
You don't? Just try to get here.

2840
01:31:17,204 --> 01:31:18,433
Where am I?

2841
01:31:18,434 --> 01:31:19,834
(So, where am I?)

2842
01:31:19,974 --> 01:31:21,373
I'm back to the starting point.

2843
01:31:21,374 --> 01:31:22,744
(Laughing)

2844
01:31:22,804 --> 01:31:24,713
Hang on. What's with this picture?

2845
01:31:24,714 --> 01:31:26,420
(He's lost at a place with no people going around.)

2846
01:31:26,444 --> 01:31:27,813
Do we have to wait for him?

2847
01:31:27,814 --> 01:31:28,814
Right.

2848
01:31:28,815 --> 01:31:30,353
Just tell him to come to the base camp.

2849
01:31:30,354 --> 01:31:31,783
- Should we do that?
- That's better.

2850
01:31:31,784 --> 01:31:33,783
- You think so?
- If he doesn't get here...

2851
01:31:33,784 --> 01:31:35,130
in three minutes, he should come to the base camp.

2852
01:31:35,154 --> 01:31:38,854
One, two, three, four, five. Done?

2853
01:31:39,094 --> 01:31:40,524
Jong Min is here.

2854
01:31:41,464 --> 01:31:43,064
It's over there. I found it.

2855
01:31:43,694 --> 01:31:45,593
I took a big lap around this area.

2856
01:31:45,594 --> 01:31:46,970
Why are you coming from that direction?

2857
01:31:46,994 --> 01:31:48,194
Why are you coming from there?

2858
01:31:48,264 --> 01:31:49,434
I made a big circle.

2859
01:31:50,064 --> 01:31:52,203
- Jong Min, take a photo alone.
- Alone.

2860
01:31:52,204 --> 01:31:54,404
Jong Min, look back as if you had found your match.

2861
01:31:54,704 --> 01:31:56,373
Look at the camera with a loving gaze.

2862
01:31:56,374 --> 01:31:57,974
(Happy)

2863
01:31:58,214 --> 01:31:59,974
- It looks great.
- Let's go.

2864
01:32:00,144 --> 01:32:03,083
All right, guys. Let's go to the base camp now.

2865
01:32:03,084 --> 01:32:04,583
- Okay.
- Let's go.

2866
01:32:04,584 --> 01:32:06,513
The alleys were beautiful on the way here.

2867
01:32:06,514 --> 01:32:08,053
- Let's go.
- Thank you.

2868
01:32:08,054 --> 01:32:09,653
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2869
01:32:09,654 --> 01:32:11,814
(We thank the citizens for helping us with the shoot.)

2870
01:32:11,894 --> 01:32:13,254
Let's go this way.

2871
01:32:13,354 --> 01:32:14,493
To the base camp.

2872
01:32:14,494 --> 01:32:15,623
Open your eyes.

2873
01:32:15,624 --> 01:32:17,934
Don't show it to me. It feels like you're teasing me.

2874
01:32:18,064 --> 01:32:22,864
(They didn't realize how important this One-Bite Ticket was.)

2875
01:32:23,004 --> 01:32:24,574
(Next episode)

2876
01:32:26,034 --> 01:32:28,574
(The winner gets to sleep in a single bed.)

2877
01:32:28,804 --> 01:32:29,844
And...

2878
01:32:29,944 --> 01:32:32,304
(The loser has to sleep alone outdoors in the bitter cold.)

2879
01:32:32,744 --> 01:32:35,384
(Sleeping alone in minus 13°C?)

2880
01:32:36,014 --> 01:32:37,454
(That's ridiculous.)

2881
01:32:37,984 --> 01:32:40,424
(The worst Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors)

2882
01:32:40,554 --> 01:32:43,624
(A Voice Is Heard From Somewhere)

2883
01:32:43,854 --> 01:32:45,554
(What is the name?)

2884
01:32:46,024 --> 01:32:47,794
(What is the name?)

2885
01:32:48,064 --> 01:32:49,163
The first member to get it right...

2886
01:32:49,164 --> 01:32:51,834
(They must catch the slightest sound...)

2887
01:32:52,534 --> 01:32:54,764
(to sleep indoors.)

2888
01:32:55,564 --> 01:32:57,574
(They must remain vigilant until the very end.)

2889
01:32:58,574 --> 01:33:01,004
(If you want to avoid sleeping outdoors, )

2890
01:33:02,004 --> 01:33:05,314
(you must catch the voice.)

2891
01:33:06,414 --> 01:33:07,714
(So, )

2892
01:33:08,284 --> 01:33:10,614
(who will end up sleeping outdoors in the bitter cold?)

2893
01:33:10,754 --> 01:33:12,053
You brats!

2894
01:33:12,054 --> 01:33:13,954
(See you next week.)
